---

<Base
  title="Thigh Lift in Houston Texas | The Oaks Plastic Surgery"
  description="Thigh Lift in Houston Texas at The Oaks Plastic Surgery. Board-certified plastic surgeons offering personalized care."
  headerTitle="Thigh Lift in Houston Texas"
  headerImage="/img/thigh-lift-hero-0.jpg"
  headerMarginBottom={60}
  canonical="https://theoaksplasticsurgery.com/thigh-lift-houston"
>
<section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
                            <p class="wow fadeInUp lead text-center">
                                A thigh lift helps to remove excess skin of the inner thighs for a slimmer, sleeker contour.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-0 pb-240">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Why do you want a Thigh Lift in Houston, Texas? </h3>
                                <p>Many of our patients who have undergone massive weight loss or have developed excess thigh skin with age are very self-conscious about this area. They complain that clothes do not fit correctly, they are unable to wear certain clothing and can have hygiene issues as well. Some patients simply desire sleeker, tighter looking thighs. A thigh lift can help you achieve this sleek contour.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What procedures are often performed along with a Thigh Lift? </h3>
                                <p>
                                    Many patients seeking a thigh lift have undergone massive weight loss and require removal of excess skin from several areas of the body including the abdomen, arms, back, breasts and face.  Dr. Danielle Andry and Dr. Nandi Wijay spent a large part of their training working with one of the innovators in breast contouring surgery after massive weight loss. They have experience in both staging and combining many of these massive weight loss body contouring procedures, and can counsel their patients on the timing and progression of these surgeries.  Please visit our massive weight loss/body contouring page for more details.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What do you want from a Thigh Lift? </h3>
                                <p>
                                    Thigh lift procedures are often a careful balance between scarring and contour. While everyone’s goal is to maximize contour and minimize scarring, sometimes a trade off must exist. The surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery want to work with you to achieve your specific goals, and perform the right procedure for you.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect during your initial consultation for a Brow Lift in Houston, Texas?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    If you are interested in a thigh lift in Houston, Texas, an appointment can be made with Dr. Danielle Andry or Dr. Nandi Wijay. You can expect the initial consultation to last an hour or more. In your consultation, Dr. Andry or Dr. Wijay will:
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Listen to your specific complaints and goals </li>
                                    <li>Perform a thorough examination, focusing on your individual anatomy and measurements</li>
                                    <li>Discuss recommendations regarding surgical or nonsurgical techniques that may help you achieve your goals</li>
                                    <li>If surgery is the right option for you, Dr. Andry or Dr. Wijay will discuss details of the surgical procedures that are offered and which approach is right for you </li>
                                    <li>Preoperative photographs will be taken and the surgical plan will be analyzed for you with use of your photographs </li>
                                    <li>The risks and benefits of surgery will be thoroughly outlined for you</li>
                                    <li>You will be given ample opportunity to ask questions from both our plastic surgeons and staff regarding thigh lift surgery and any other surgical or nonsurgical procedures you may be interested in</li>
                                    <li>You will be sent home with a packet of information regarding thigh lift surgery, including a detailed consent form and instructions for before and after your plastic surgery procedure</li>
                                </ul>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect the day of your thigh lift procedure? </h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    The day of your surgery, Dr. Danielle Andry or Dr. Nandi Wijay will meet you in the preoperative area to go over any last minute questions or concerns you may have. They will make preoperative markings, and will perform extensive checks with attention to detail ensuring high quality care and safety. You will meet the anesthesiologist and their team, as well as the members of our operative team.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    During the procedure, our doctors pay meticulous attention to detail, and work as a team to ensure a great result with a focus on safety and quality. Your family will be updated of your status periodically, and will be able to talk with the plastic surgeon one-on-one after the procedure is completed.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
